<h1 style="color:#4ffff7">foxhole stats population and queue data</h1>

<p>
 <b style="color:#fff562;">Here we have 49 Wars (War #63 - #111 , 3.5 years) of new data which: </b></p>
 Updates: watch a <a target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ai8igpz5uFg">youtube video</a> on the topic by "Robert LuvsGames"<br /><br />
 <ul>
 <li>Strongly suggests population imbalance plays one of the biggest roles in war outcome</li>
 <li>There is currently no effective method for mitigating this and many wars have been unfairly unbalanced</li>
 <li>The combined man-hours for this period is 36,577,071 hours or 4233.5 years ~ 52 lifetimes (imagine what else that could do)</li>
 <li>Data was collected from an unpublished api, that became more and more widely known to exist, though afaik most only thought it had queue data</li>
 <li>Several people asked me to add the queue data to FHS, but I just fobbed them off as I knew there was more than queue data there and that if I added it it would lead to it being removed.</li>
 <li>I have for years tried to advocate that devs should make a global player split count public after it was 'accidentally' taken away in the process of removing per region pop splits and the creation of warapi</li>
 <li><a href="https://war-service-live.foxholeservices.com/external/shardStatus" target="_blank">This api</a> was removed in an update after war 111, I have since found these new apis: 
 <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/config/client_config.json" target="_blank">1</a>, 
  <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/config/client_config_internal.json" target="_blank">2</a>, 
   <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/config/client_config_devbranch.json" target="_blank">3</a>, 
    <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/config/client_config_iteration.json" target="_blank">4</a>, 
     <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/newsfeed/news.json" target="_blank">5</a>, 
      <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/newsfeed/news_internal.json" target="_blank">6</a>, 
       <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foxhole-updates/newsfeed/news_iteration.json" target="_blank">7</a>
 </li>
 <li>To read more history of population data and foxhole, visit: <a href="https://www.patreon.com/foxholestats/about" target="_blank">https://www.patreon.com/foxholestats/about</a></li>
 <li>Click here if you would like to see <a href="https://foxholestats.com/drawProto.php" target="_blank">the original hidden stats panel</a> I made to monitor wars</li>
 <li>Discuss here: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/foxholegame/comments/1c53mib/view_49_wars_35_years_of_until_now_unreleased/">reddit</a> or <a target="_blank" href="https://discord.gg/dnegnws">discord</a>, download the  <a href="https://github.com/hayden-t/foxholestats-resources/raw/main/warapi_logs.zip" >raw data here</a>
 </ul>

 <p>
 The data is now integrated into the main FHS website graphs:<br /> Here are some example observations I made on some random wars to help you learn what to look for:<Br /> (and below that, is a table of imbalance data summaries)
 
